---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Company | BeaconGuard Assurance"
  description="BeaconGuard builds runtime control infrastructure for AI-assisted regulated operations across healthcare operations, financial services workflows, and regulated internal automation."
>
  <section>
    <h1>Company</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      BeaconGuard builds runtime control infrastructure for AI-assisted regulated operations. The product deploys alongside existing enterprise applications as an inline policy enforcement boundary, focusing on deterministic policy enforcement before model execution and evidence preservation after every decision.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Mission</h2>
    <p>
      BeaconGuard exists to make execution-boundary authorization dependable, reviewable, and operationally practical for high-risk enterprise AI workflows.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Initial Focus</h2>
    <p>
      BeaconGuard is initially focused on healthcare operations, financial services workflows, and regulated internal automation.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Why BeaconGuard exists</h2>
    <p>
      Enterprises want to adopt AI in sensitive workflows, but model behavior is probabilistic. Control ownership, auditability, and policy enforcement cannot be left to prompt design alone. BeaconGuard provides an inline runtime control boundary and reviewable evidence layer around AI-bound requests while existing systems continue to own workflow logic and records.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
